text.section:
The Executive Director is the chief administrative officer and secretary of the Authority and shall:
direct and supervise the administrative affairs and activities of the Authority, in accordance with its regulations and policies;
attend the meetings of the Authority;
keep minutes of all proceedings of the Authority;
approve all accounts for salaries, per diem payments, and all allowable expenses of the Authority, its employees, and its consultants;
approve all expenses incidental to the operation of the Authority;
report and make recommendations to the Authority on the merits and status of any proposed facility; and
perform the other duties that the Authority requires to carry out this subtitle.
